<HL>
   Continental Airlines' Traffic
</HL>
<DATE>
09/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   CTA
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   HOUSTON -- Continental Airlines, a unit of Continental
Airlines Holdings, said August traffic rose 0.3% to 4.11
billion revenue passenger miles, from 4.10 billion revenue
passenger miles in the year-earlier period. A revenue
passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one mile. Load
factor, or the percentage of available seats that are
occupied, was 69.2% for the month, compared with 71.5% last
year.
   For the year-to-date, Continental said it flew 26.67
billion revenue passenger miles, a 0.4% increase from 26.58
billion a year ago. Load factor fell to 61.8% from 61.9%.
</LP>
