<IN>
BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)
</IN>
<LP>
   AMSTERDAM -- The number of business bankruptcies in the
Netherlands in the first eight months of this year declined
4.5% to 2,351 from 2,461 a year earlier, the Dutch Central
Bureau of Statistics said. In August alone, 268 businesses
failed, down 7.3% from 289 in August 1989.
