<HL>
   Canada's Housing Starts
</HL>
<DATE>
09/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C13
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian housing starts declined 7% in August to
a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 163,000 units, from a
July level of 175,000 units, Canadian Mortgage &amp; Housing
Corp., a government agency, said.
   The corporation attributed the August decline to high
mortgage rates and a sharp deterioration in consumer
confidence. It expects housing starts to decline further in
coming months.
</LP>
