<HL>
   AMR Unit Air Traffic Climbs
</HL>
<DATE>
09/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10
</SO>
<CO>
   AMR
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   FORT WORTH, Texas -- American Airlines, a unit of AMR
Corp., said August traffic rose 2.6% to 7.57 billion revenue
passenger miles from 7.38 billion miles a year earlier. A
revenue passenger mile is one paying passenger carried one
mile.
   Load factor, or the percentage of available seats that are
occupied, for the month fell to 68.9% from 72.3% a year
earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the year-to-date, American said it flew 51.73 billion
revenue passenger miles, a 4.1% increase from 49.71 billion
miles a year earlier. Load factor fell to 63.5% from 65.2%.
</TEXT>
