   Newsprint-Mill Negotiations
   Over Sale Are Broken Off
</HL>
<DATE>
09/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9
</SO>
<CO>
   KMB NYTA
</CO>
<IN>
MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)
RAW AND FINISHED PAPER PRODUCTS (PAP)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Kimberly-Clark Corp. and New York Times Co. said they
broke off negotiations to sell their jointly owned newsprint
mill to Kruger Inc. after the Montreal-based paper company
failed to secure financing for the purchase.
   The companies say Spruce Falls Power &amp; Paper Co. in remote
Kapuskasing, Ont., remains for sale. "We are disappointed,"
the companies said in a joint statement. "We felt that Kruger
was in a better position to capitalize on the strengths of
Spruce Falls."
