company, will not reverse the $44 million charge it took in
the second quarter anticipating the sale of the mill. Losses
at the mill have hurt both companies. A Kruger spokesman
declined to comment.
   Kimberly-Clark stock fell 12.5 cents yesterday to close at
$75.50 a share in New York Stock Exchange composite trading,
while New York Times stock also fell 12.5 cents a share to
close at $19 in American Stock Exchange composite trading.
