</CO>
<IN>
RAW AND FINISHED PAPER PRODUCTS (PAP)
</IN>
<LP>
   Abitibi-Price Inc., a Toronto-based newsprint concern,
said the Canadian Paperworkers Union broke off contract
talks, as a strike at seven of the company's paper mills
continued.
   An Abitibi official said the union ended negotiations in
Toronto and indicated it will ask its members to vote on the
company's latest offer. Union officials were traveling and
couldn't be reached for comment.
