</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A13
</SO>
<CO>
   J.FJH
</CO>
<IN>
AUTOMOBILES (AUT)
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   Fuji Heavy Industries Ltd., maker of Subaru automobiles,
said that it won't be paying its previously planned interim
dividend for the half-year period ending Sept. 30.
   Although unconsolidated sales are expected to see a
healthy 10% increase in the half year from the prior period,
the Tokyo-based company said that an operating loss will be
likely because of cost increases and the expense of a sales
promotion for both domestic and overseas markets.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company paid a dividend totaling 8 yen (six cents) a
share during the prior full fiscal year.
   Fuji Heavy said it is in the process of restructuring
operations in order to boost performance.
