<HL>
   Penn Central Holders
   Of 11.3 Million Shares
   Act on Tender Offer
</HL>
<DATE>
09/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   PC
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)
</IN>
<LP>
   CINCINNATI -- Penn Central Corp., an industrial, defense,
insurance and energy concern, said 11,347,000 of its common
shares were tendered in response to its offer to buy back 11
million shares at $23 each. The offer expired at midnight
Monday.
   Under the offer for 11 million shares, Penn Central is to
buy first from odd-lot holders, who tendered 26,000 shares,
and then will buy 97% of the shares tendered by each other
holder.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Of the 11,347,000 shares tendered, 3,047,000 were tendered
subject to guarantees of delivery. If some of those shares
aren't tendered and the total tendered falls to 11 million or
below, Penn Central will buy back all the tendered shares.
   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,
Penn Central closed at $22.75 a share, down 25 cents.
</TEXT>
